    "overview_number": 1,
    "overview_title": "Many Ways to Measure",
    "overview_subtitle": "Using Ratio Reasoning to Convert Units",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students compare measurements within and between the U.S. customary and metric systems. They express conversion equations as a ratio in fractional form and use ratio reasoning in double number lines, ratio tables, and proportions to convert units. Students make sense of unit analysis and use this method to convert units."
  },
